Perfectly positioned with dual access points along Church Place and Quebec Street, this is an incredible opportunity to snap up a charming, historic piece of Port Adelaide. The site has been home to Williams Laser Cutting and Fabrication for over 50 years and its current layout offers a buyer potential for future holding income. The property offers a blank canvas for future development, with favourbale Regional Centre (Mainstreet) zoning in the City if Port Adelaide Enfield.

- Large land area of approximately 1,399 sqm* spread across 5 certificates of title
- Zoned Regional Centre (Mainstreet) offering a range of future development opportunities (STCC)
- Dual access along Church Place and Quebec Street
- Combined frontage of approximately 35 metres onto Church Place
- 1,224sqm* of existing building
- Port Adelaide is currently an emerging location with significant economic upside
